# Trivy CVE ignore list
# Format: <CVE-ID> [expiry-date] [# comment]
#
# CVEs listed here are acknowledged but have no available fix in the
# current base image (python:3.14-slim-bookworm / Debian Bookworm).
# Each entry must be reviewed and renewed periodically.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CVE-2025-70873 | HIGH | CVSS 7.5 | libsqlite3-0
# SQLite ≤3.51.1 zipfileInflate function in the zipfile extension allows
# attackers to obtain heap memory via a crafted ZIP file (info-disclosure).
# Status: NO FIX available in Debian Bookworm as of 2026-03-16.
# Workaround: libsqlite3-0 upgraded to latest available backport via
#             apt-get upgrade in Dockerfile. Will be removed once Debian
#             Bookworm ships a patched sqlite3 package.
# Reference: https://cve.circl.lu/cve/CVE-2025-70873
CVE-2025-70873

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
